              <p align="justify"><strong>MailerMailer Releases Email Marketing Report: H2 2006</strong></p>\r\n                        <p align="justify">Rockville, MD, 02/20/2006 -- MailerMailer, an email list management company that provides web-based services for creating and tracking opt-in newsletters and campaigns, recently released its Email Marketing Metrics Report for the last half (H2) of 2005.</p>\r\n                        <p align="justify">The report details email marketing performance by industry based on over 200 million messages sent by MailerMailer customers between July 1 and December 31, 2005. Although it reveals a slight decline in overall unique open and click rates from the first half (H1) of 2005, several industries experienced improved click rates.</p>\r\n                        <p align="justify"><strong>Email Marketing Metrics </strong><br />\r\n                        <br />\r\n                        ·&#160;&#160;The unique open rate for emails sent by all industries in H2 was 19.81%, compared to 21.77% for those sent in the first half of the year. <br />\r\n                        ·&#160;&#160;The average click rate for email messages sent by all industries in H2 2005 was 3.30% - down from 3.59% for ones sent in H1. <br />\r\n                        ·&#160;&#160;Once again, the industries that earned the highest open rates in H2 2005 were Government, Religious, and Banking. <br />\r\n                        ·&#160;&#160;Subscribers clicked more often on email campaigns sent by organizations in the Retail, Banking, and Computing industries. <br />\r\n                        ·&#160;&#160;Industries that received the largest increase in click rates from the first half of the year were: Medical, Religious, and Real Estate. <br />\r\n                        <br />\r\n                        The Email Marketing Metrics Report includes unique open and click-through rates by industry; bounce and delivery trends; open and click rates by day of the week; and the effect of personalization on open and click rates. It contains a breakdown of metrics that can serve as benchmarks for email marketers.</p>\r\n                        </td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n                <tbody>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td height="53" class="STYLE2">Number of clients</td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n            <table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="1" bgcolor="#CCCCCC">\r\n                <tbody>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td width="32%" bgcolor="#a9a8a8" class="tabname">Chient Name</td>\r\n                        <td width="42%" bgcolor="#a9a8a8" class="tabname">Address</td>\r\n                        <td width="26%" bgcolor="#a9a8a8" class="tabname">Data</td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" class="tabcon">C. Marcelo Aldaz</td>\r\n                        <td bgcolor="#E4E4E4" class="tabcon">UT M.D. Anderson Cancer Ctr</td>\r\n                        <td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" class="tabcon">Sep 2, 2006 10:05</td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" class="tabcon">C. Marcelo Aldaz</td>\r\n                        <td bgcolor="#E4E4E4" class="tabcon">Univ. of California Berkeley, CA</td>\r\n                        <td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" class="tabcon">Sep 2, 2006 10:05</td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" class="tabcon">C. Marcelo Aldaz</td>\r\n                        <td bgcolor="#E4E4E4" class="tabcon">Universidad de  Valencia, SPAIN</td>\r\n                        <td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" class="tabcon">Sep 2, 2006 10:05</td>\r\n                 